In criminal law, an examination of a person's house or other buildings or premises, or of his person, with a view to the discovery and removal of contraband or illicit or stolen property, or some evidence of guilt to be used in the prosecution of a criminal action for some crime or offense with which he is charged. 

Source: [VA Journey Through Justice Glossary](http://www.jtj.courts.state.va.us/resources_glossary.html)